This is neat looking bar with a western style. We stopped in to watch the Packer game on our way through. They have 5 large TVs over the bar making it great for watching sports. The bathrooms were clean and the food was good. I had the Reuben which could have used more kraut and dressing, but was good regardless. The beer was good as well and they have a decent selection. The reason I couldn't give 5 stars is due to the fact that I am a beer drinker that prefers draft beer. They do not have any taps. Other than that, I would definitely recommend this venue.

We came to the bar at 1:50am and we were all served drinks. 2 minutes later we were told we needed to leave. We asked for drink tickets for the drinks they let us buy and then kicked us out before we could drink. They refused. The bartender who told us to leave was so drunk she slurred all of her words and couldn't form complete sentences. She began to physically shove my siblings and I. As we were leaving, 5 other workers who were also extremely intoxicated came up and got rough with us. All we did was ask for drink tickets and try to leave. Even while outside the establishment, the workers continued to approach us. Someone had to phsycially carry a worker to get them away from us. Police got involved. I have no idea why anyone would ever patron this bar. I've never seen such poor service or felt so physically unsafe in a space. I strongly recommend you chose one of the other amazing bars in the area.
